name: Winnie Hou
headline: Product Design @ Duolingo
creator: True
school_1: University of Washington Human Centered Design & Engineering
bio:
Growing up in Taiwan, I didn't have many opportunities to work in collaborative or expressive environments. Working in retail transformed me from an introvert into a collaborative, communicative, curiosity seeker. As I delve into product design, I’ve learned how much collaboration through idea sharing has impacted my growth as a designer. My experiences have all shaped the designer I am today, helping me become empathetic, inclusive, and open-minded. I make it a point to learn people’s stories and understand how I can be a part of them. 

So, what’s your story?

name: Jaylyn Jones
headline: University Recruiter - Software Engineering & Product Management Internships at Duolingo 💚 | Applications now open!
creator: True
bio:
I’m a university recruiter who’s all about connecting early career talent to real opportunities and keeping it real while I do it.

With a background in higher education, I know what it’s like to chase big goals with limited info. That’s why I’m big on transparency, real conversations, and building a hiring process that doesn't suck.

When I’m not recruiting, you’ll find me creating career content to break down what’s really happening behind the scenes. Resumes, interviews, offers  I’m here to help you stop guessing and start making moves.

At the end of the day, I’m in this to open doors, share what I know, and help people bet on themselves, because your next big opportunity shouldn’t be a mystery.

📩 Booking inquiries:
If you’re reaching out about brand partnerships, speaking engagements, or media opportunities, please email bookjaylyn@gmail.com.

Students and job seekers: This inbox is NOT for career advice, resume reviews, or job search help. I promise, emailing me there will not make you stand out in a good way.
